# Themis Phase-3 greenfield node — example environment configuration (CONVENTIONS.md R2).
#
# Every deployable node (evidence / registry / knowledge / governance / communication /
# intelligence) reads its configuration from the environment. Every option is documented
# here inline — there is no separate config reference that can drift. Copy this file, fill in
# the values for the node you are running, and export them (or load with your process
# manager). Secrets are referenced by name, never inlined.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Shared — observability (R1). Read identically by every node from the shared
# internal/platform/observability package. Console logging is always on; OpenTelemetry log
# export is enabled only when THEMIS_OTLP_LOGS_ENDPOINT is set.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Minimum log severity. One of: debug | info | warn | error. Default: info.
THEMIS_LOG_LEVEL=info

# Console log encoding. One of: json (machine-readable, prod) | console (human-readable, dev).
# Default: json.
THEMIS_LOG_FORMAT=json

# OTLP/HTTP logs collector endpoint, host:port (e.g. otel-collector:4318). When empty, OTel
# log export is OFF and only the console channel is active (nothing external needed to run).
# Default: "" (console-only).
THEMIS_OTLP_LOGS_ENDPOINT=

# Send to the OTLP endpoint over http instead of https ("1" to enable) — for local collectors.
# Default: 0 (https).
THEMIS_OTLP_INSECURE=0

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Shared — datastore. Required by every node that persists.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# PostgreSQL DSN. REQUIRED. Provide via your secret store, not a committed file.
THEMIS_DATABASE_DSN=postgres://themis:CHANGEME@localhost:5432/themis?sslmode=disable

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Per-node options (set the block for the node you are running). Each node's config struct
# in cmd/<node>/main.go documents these inline as well.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Evidence (cmd/evidence)
THEMIS_EVIDENCE_ADDR=:8081                 # HTTP listen address. Default :8081.
THEMIS_EVIDENCE_MIGRATE=0                  # "1" to apply Evidence migrations on startup.
THEMIS_EVIDENCE_DEV_PURGE=0                # "1" to expose DELETE /dev/evidence (dev only).
# THEMIS_EVIDENCE_KNOWN_RELEASES=          # dev only: comma-separated release ids for the stub SubjectRef; empty = registry-backed.

# Registry (cmd/registry)
THEMIS_REGISTRY_ADDR=:8082                 # HTTP listen address. Default :8082.
THEMIS_REGISTRY_MIGRATE=0                  # "1" to apply Registry migrations on startup.
THEMIS_REGISTRY_DEV_PURGE=0                # "1" to expose DELETE /dev/registry (dev only).

# Governance (cmd/governance)
THEMIS_GOVERNANCE_ADDR=:8083               # HTTP listen address. Default :8083.
THEMIS_GOVERNANCE_MIGRATE=0                # "1" to apply Governance migrations on startup.
THEMIS_GOVERNANCE_DEV_PURGE=0              # "1" to expose DELETE /dev/governance (dev only).

# Communication (cmd/communication)
THEMIS_COMMUNICATION_ADDR=:8084            # HTTP listen address. Default :8084.
THEMIS_GOVERNANCE_URL=http://localhost:8083 # Governance read-API base URL (for GetPosition).
THEMIS_COMMUNICATION_MIGRATE=0             # "1" to apply Communication migrations on startup.
THEMIS_COMMUNICATION_DEV_PURGE=0           # "1" to expose DELETE /dev/communication (dev only).

# Intelligence Gateway (cmd/intelligence) — the OPTIONAL AI plane (D13). STATELESS (no DB).
# Deploy this service ONLY when AI is enabled; when disabled, do not run it and set the
# consuming-context gate below. Disabled ≡ unavailable — the pipeline is correct with AI off.
THEMIS_INTELLIGENCE_ADDR=:8086             # HTTP listen address. Default :8086.
# THEMIS_GOVERNANCE_URL=...                # (shared, above) Governance read-API base URL — Finding grounding.
THEMIS_KNOWLEDGE_URL=http://localhost:8085 # Knowledge read-API base URL — Faultline enrichment grounding.
THEMIS_OLLAMA_URL=http://localhost:11434   # Ollama base URL (OpenAI-compatible). Mac dev: native Ollama (Metal GPU); cluster: the Ollama container Service.
THEMIS_INTELLIGENCE_MODEL=llama3.1:8b      # Pinned model. Default llama3.1:8b (16GB Apple Silicon-friendly).
THEMIS_INTELLIGENCE_PROVIDER=              # "fake" = deterministic dev/CI provider (no model); empty = ollama.

# Disable gate (D13). The consuming context (Governance) wires the real vs a no-op Intelligence
# client from these — one switch, no call-site flags. Off = zero AI footprint.
# THEMIS_INTELLIGENCE_ENABLED=1            # global gate.
# THEMIS_GOVERNANCE_AI_ENABLED=0           # Governance-side gate: "1" wires the real client, else the no-op.
# THEMIS_INTELLIGENCE_URL=http://localhost:8086  # Governance → Intelligence reactive-API base URL (when enabled).
